  "text": "Seaweeds are macroscopic flora that originates on the rocky bottom in relatively shallow coastal water. These are prospective renewable resources in the marine realm with about 6000 species identified so far. They are categorized into three different classes such as Green Seaweed (Chlorophyceae), Brown Seaweed (Phaeophyceae) and Red Seaweed (Rhodophyceae). According to Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) [2016] , the global production of seaweed has crossed 30 million tons of fresh weight year À1 with an average value of $400 tons per dry weight [CITATION_1] .",
